@startuml 03_sequence_step
' Diagramme de sequence : un pas couple hyperbolique-elliptique.
' Montre l'INTERACTION entre les couches (qui appelle qui) sur un pas SSP-RK2.

title adc_cpp -- sequence d'un pas couple (Coupler::advance, SSP-RK2)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #444444
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #F4F6F8
skinparam participantBorderColor #08519C

actor "boucle de temps" as Loop
participant "Coupler" as C
participant "Elliptic\n(GeometricMG)" as MG
participant "assemble_rhs" as RHS
participant "Model\n(Diocotron)" as M
participant "for_each_cell\n<<seam>>" as SEAM

Loop -> C : advance(U, dt)
activate C

== 1. resolution elliptique ==
C -> MG : rhs() <- model.elliptic_rhs(U)
C -> MG : solve()
activate MG
MG --> C : phi (warm-start)
deactivate MG
C -> C : aux = (phi, grad phi)

== 2. etage RK : R = -div F + S ==
C -> RHS : assemble_rhs(model, U, aux, R)
activate RHS
RHS -> SEAM : for_each_cell(box, lambda)
activate SEAM
SEAM -> M : flux(U, aux, dir)
SEAM -> M : max_wave_speed(U, aux, dir)
SEAM -> M : source(U, aux)
M --> SEAM : valeurs ponctuelles
SEAM --> RHS : R rempli
deactivate SEAM
RHS --> C : R
deactivate RHS
C -> C : U1 = U + dt * R

== 3. second etage (re-solve phi pour U1) ==
C -> MG : solve()  (PerStage)
C -> RHS : assemble_rhs(model, U1, aux, R)
C -> C : U = 1/2 (U + U1 + dt R)

C --> Loop : U avance
deactivate C

note over SEAM, M
  La physique (Model) est appelee
  point par point dans le seam.
  Le seam choisit serie / OpenMP /
  Kokkos a la compilation -- le Model
  ne le sait pas.
end note

@enduml
